==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Saxon [[hugi]], Old High German [[hugu]], [[hugi]], Old Norse [[hugr]], Gothic [[𐌷𐌿𐌲𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'hyje/}}

===Noun===
'''hyġe''' ''m'' (plural '''[[hygas|hyġas]]''')
# [[mind]], [[spirit]], [[heart]], [[soul]]
#:''Forþon is min hyge geomor.''  Therefore my heart is sorrowful.  (‘The Wife's Lament’)

